# Implement Sample Unit Tests — Meridian Backend

This plan introduces xUnit-based unit test projects for each microservice in the Meridian Backend solution. The goal is to give the QA engineer a working test framework with representative sample tests covering controller logic and service-layer logic for every service.

---

## Current State: No Tests Exist

| Service | Path | Test Folder? |
|---|---|---|
| DeliveryService | `src/DeliveryService/DeliveryService.API` | ❌ None |
| VehicleService | `src/VehicleService/VehicleService.API` | ❌ None |
| DriverService | `src/DriverService/DriverService.API` | ❌ None |
| AssignmentService | `src/AssignmentService/AssignmentService.API` | ❌ None |
| RouteService | `src/RouteService/RouteService.API` | ❌ None |
| TrackingService | `src/TrackingService/TrackingService.API` | ❌ None |

---

## Test Stack

| Package | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `xunit` | Test framework |
| `xunit.runner.visualstudio` | VS/dotnet test runner |
| `Moq` | Mocking dependencies (services, repos, IHubContext) |
| `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing` | For controller unit tests via `WebApplicationFactory` |
| `coverlet.collector` | Code coverage |

> All test projects will target **.NET 10.0** to match the production services.

